501
00:25:44,810 --> 00:25:46,210
What about Browne?

502
00:25:46,845 --> 00:25:49,178
She may have as much
problem being a leader as Murphy,

503
00:25:49,248 --> 00:25:50,614
and without his gifts.

504
00:25:51,116 --> 00:25:52,778
She has her own gifts.

505
00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:55,514
Yeah, dealing with
patients and their families.

506
00:25:55,587 --> 00:25:58,421
But with her colleagues,
she can be insecure.

507
00:25:59,258 --> 00:26:01,218
Her assertiveness has
always been a question mark.

508
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,354
They've all got areas
that need improving,

509
00:26:03,429 --> 00:26:06,058
but I've gotten to know Browne a
bit better these past few months.

510
00:26:07,499 --> 00:26:09,229
She's stronger than she looks.

511
00:26:11,370 --> 00:26:13,737
When's the last time you saw
anyone dig a ditch in a suit?

512
00:26:13,806 --> 00:26:15,604
Surgeons don't dig ditches.

513
00:26:15,674 --> 00:26:18,701
They help people at the most
vulnerable time in their life.

514
00:26:19,211 --> 00:26:21,806
And you shouldn't
take the responsibility on

515
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,542
if you're not fully
committed to it.

516
00:26:24,783 --> 00:26:26,547
You're entering a new
phase in your career,

517
00:26:26,618 --> 00:26:27,950
a position of authority.

518
00:26:28,020 --> 00:26:30,387
Maybe my clothes are
making you feel disrespected.

519
00:26:30,456 --> 00:26:35,224
But the truth is, I just hate wearing
anything that makes me feel like...

520
00:26:36,562 --> 00:26:37,562
a suit.

521
00:26:38,897 --> 00:26:42,800
Great news. I was able to get
Sowinski on anesthesia for tomorrow.

522
00:26:42,868 --> 00:26:44,632
Uh, why? What happened to Foley?

523
00:26:44,703 --> 00:26:46,303
Nothing. I just think
Sowinski's better.

524
00:26:46,338 --> 00:26:48,239
And we definitely
need the A-team on this.

525
00:26:48,307 --> 00:26:49,434
Yeah, I agree.

526
00:26:49,508 --> 00:26:52,603
Which is why I went out
of my way to get Foley.

527
00:26:52,678 --> 00:26:54,772
But Foley doesn't do
well under pressure.

528
00:26:54,847 --> 00:26:56,213
- Remember that ti...
- Morgan.

529
00:26:57,015 --> 00:26:57,914
You need to butt out.

530
00:26:57,983 --> 00:26:59,918
You're not a surgeon.
This is not your job.

531
00:27:01,086 --> 00:27:04,420
My job is to help my patient
through the entire treatment process.

532
00:27:04,490 --> 00:27:07,619
The best anesthesiologist for
transplant surgery is Sowinski.

533
00:27:07,693 --> 00:27:10,133
I've already cleared it with
Lim, so that's who it's gonna be.

534
00:27:10,696 --> 00:27:11,823
Deal with it.

535
00:27:21,773 --> 00:27:23,435
Are you mad at me?

536
00:27:27,012 --> 00:27:30,141
I said your voice
doesn't bother me.

537
00:27:30,849 --> 00:27:32,715
It was a compliment.

538
00:27:33,285 --> 00:27:36,585
Actually, what you said is that
you love my breasts so much

539
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:39,750
that with the help of
noise-canceling headphones,

540
00:27:39,825 --> 00:27:42,226
you're willing to put up
with my annoying voice.

541
00:27:43,362 --> 00:27:44,386
Yes.

542
00:27:45,464 --> 00:27:46,488
Not a compliment.

543
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:48,966
Oh.

544
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:52,098
- So you are mad at me?
- I'm not mad, Shaun.

545
00:27:52,171 --> 00:27:54,531
I'm just busy trying to keep
like a billion bots and hackers

546
00:27:54,573 --> 00:27:55,573
out of our network.

547
00:27:57,242 --> 00:28:00,144
Actually, no, I'm not
doing that. Gonna go home.

548
00:28:00,212 --> 00:28:05,344
You want to have some tequila,
stat? We also have some pizza left.

549
00:28:05,417 --> 00:28:09,912
- No. I don't want tequila or pizza.
- That must mean you're mad.

550
00:28:09,988 --> 00:28:14,619
I'm just upset. And confused.

551
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:17,629
And I really don't think there
is anything you can do about it,

552
00:28:17,696 --> 00:28:21,064
so you just need to stop
trying and leave me alone.

553
00:28:30,175 --> 00:28:34,010
- She's not mad at me.
- She's definitely mad at you.

554
00:28:34,079 --> 00:28:36,913
She doesn't usually
hide what she thinks.

555
00:28:36,982 --> 00:28:38,575
She's not mad at him.

556
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:42,214
She knows how
he is, how he talks.

557
00:28:42,854 --> 00:28:44,789
She's mad at
herself. And scared.

558
00:28:46,024 --> 00:28:47,925
We all have stuff that
we're insecure about.

559
00:28:48,327 --> 00:28:49,967
That's why it's so
risky falling in love.

560
00:28:52,898 --> 00:28:54,618
We all hope that when
we let our guard down,

561
00:28:54,666 --> 00:28:56,931
it's for the one person
that doesn't see our flaws.

562
00:29:00,906 --> 00:29:03,774
So, what do I do?

563
00:29:04,876 --> 00:29:07,311
You were being honest.
You can't apologize that away.

564
00:29:08,213 --> 00:29:11,253
You gotta figure out what she needs
to feel secure in the relationship again.

565
00:29:14,519 --> 00:29:16,283
Don't look at me. I'm single.

566
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:24,555
It's not my place to
comment on your personal life.

567
00:29:24,630 --> 00:29:26,258
You have an
opinion. Let's hear it.

568
00:29:26,832 --> 00:29:27,832
Fine.

569
00:29:29,668 --> 00:29:31,159
Can you zoom in
on her skull base?

570
00:29:31,236 --> 00:29:32,534
I can, but why?

571
00:29:32,604 --> 00:29:35,665
We're worried about her heart
and metabolic abnormalities.

572
00:29:36,308 --> 00:29:38,436
We shouldn't be. Not anymore.

573
00:29:38,977 --> 00:29:41,572
You and Dr. Murphy
were both wrong.

574
00:29:41,647 --> 00:29:44,116
She doesn't have a
cardiac or metabolic issue.

575
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:47,345
She has poor blood flow
in the artery supplying blood

576
00:29:47,419 --> 00:29:49,513
to the area of her brain
that controls consciousness.

577
00:29:49,588 --> 00:29:52,387
A small clot in her
artery of Percheron.

578
00:29:52,457 --> 00:29:56,485
If we don't remove it fast,
she's never going to wake up.

579
00:30:08,106 --> 00:30:09,574
That's amazing.

580
00:30:09,641 --> 00:30:10,870
No, it's not.

581
00:30:11,510 --> 00:30:14,912
The heart's totally outside
of the body and still beating.

582
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,744
It's like it has a
mind of its own.

583
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:19,250
She should've started
the reimplantation by now.

584
00:30:19,318 --> 00:30:21,082
Is everything okay, Dr. Lim?

585
00:30:21,153 --> 00:30:23,952
The tumor had tendrils
invading the right atrial wall.

586
00:30:24,022 --> 00:30:27,424
We took so much tissue to get a
clear margin, there's not enough left

587
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:29,518
to reconstruct his
heart's inflow chambers.

588
00:30:29,594 --> 00:30:30,892
How about expanded PTFE graft?

589
00:30:30,962 --> 00:30:33,074
There's not enough atrial
remnant to attach the graft.

590
00:30:33,098 --> 00:30:34,361
You can use the septal wall.

591
00:30:34,433 --> 00:30:36,311
He's got dense
conduction fibers there.

592
00:30:36,335 --> 00:30:38,212
- It could cause heart arrhythmias.
- Not if you...

593
00:30:38,236 --> 00:30:40,515
He's got low arterial pressure.

594
00:30:40,539 --> 00:30:42,317
He's springing leaks
at the cannulation sites.

595
00:30:42,341 --> 00:30:44,537
It's a bleeding disorder
caused by prolonged bypass.

596
00:30:44,609 --> 00:30:46,169
You need to get his
heart back in ASAP.

597
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:49,078
Morgan, we can't put the heart
back in with two missing chambers.

598
00:30:56,722 --> 00:30:58,399
It's a rare complication,

599
00:30:58,423 --> 00:31:00,688
but a blood clot is
a risk in any surgery.

600
00:31:00,759 --> 00:31:03,104
It's too deep in the
brain for open surgery.

601
00:31:03,128 --> 00:31:05,427
If we go rooting around in
there, we'd damage the PCA.

602
00:31:05,497 --> 00:31:06,521
We'd kill her.

603
00:31:07,032 --> 00:31:09,592
We could inject a
dissolving agent into the clot.

604
00:31:09,668 --> 00:31:13,662
There's a 50% probability
it won't fully dissolve,

605
00:31:13,739 --> 00:31:15,571
which could leave her
with permanent weakness

606
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:16,869
and cognitive difficulties.

607
00:31:16,942 --> 00:31:18,934
Assuming she wakes up at all.

608
00:31:23,382 --> 00:31:26,716
We need to remove the
clot with a stent retriever.

609
00:31:28,587 --> 00:31:30,852
If we rupture the
posterior cerebral artery,

610
00:31:30,922 --> 00:31:32,413
she'll die on the table.

611
00:31:34,626 --> 00:31:36,527
Or total recovery.

612
00:31:37,796 --> 00:31:41,597
That's how she came into this
hospital. That's how she's leaving.

613
00:31:44,603 --> 00:31:46,128
Prep her for stent retrieval.

614
00:31:48,006 --> 00:31:50,942
Hanging platelets and
fresh frozen plasma.

615
00:31:51,009 --> 00:31:52,807
His pressure is
still in the toilet.

616
00:31:52,878 --> 00:31:54,540
But the bleeding
is slowing down.

617
00:31:54,613 --> 00:31:55,808
Not for long.

618
00:31:55,881 --> 00:31:58,009
Small intestine submucosa
has the right compliance

619
00:31:58,083 --> 00:31:59,608
to shape the
chamber walls, but...

620
00:31:59,684 --> 00:32:01,448
There isn't enough to
cover that much area.

621
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:04,115
Use too little and he'll
have heart failure in a month.

622
00:32:04,189 --> 00:32:05,987
I know. That's the "but."

623
00:32:06,057 --> 00:32:08,336
How thick is his deep fascia?
If it's over 2 millimeters...

624
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:10,761
Morgan, get out.

625
00:32:11,396 --> 00:32:14,059
- I'm sorry. I'll be quiet.
- No, you won't. You can't.

626
00:32:14,132 --> 00:32:15,794
So leave the OR gallery.

627
00:32:18,203 --> 00:32:19,203
Now.

628
00:32:25,444 --> 00:32:28,778
We need 2.6-millimeter-thick
tissue with perfect compliance

629
00:32:28,847 --> 00:32:31,339
for arterial filling and
contractile pressures.

630
00:32:31,416 --> 00:32:34,614
If it was just the valve, we'd
use a bovine pericardial graft.

631
00:32:34,686 --> 00:32:38,555
But cow heart tissue is not durable
enough to do an entire chamber.

632
00:32:38,623 --> 00:32:40,615
But pig bladder
tissue is just right.

633
00:32:41,092 --> 00:32:43,186
I've used it for bladder
reconstructive surgeries,

634
00:32:43,261 --> 00:32:44,456
but never hearts.

635
00:32:44,529 --> 00:32:46,828
Let's rebuild the
entire atrial walls with it.

636
00:32:47,566 --> 00:32:49,076
Get down to the
tissue procurement lab

637
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:51,262
and get 200 centimeters
of porcine bladder tissue.

638
00:33:00,846 --> 00:33:03,042
Her EEG delta waves
are slowing further.

639
00:33:03,114 --> 00:33:05,811
She only has one vessel
feeding her thalamus.

640
00:33:06,785 --> 00:33:08,385
That's why the clot
landed where it did.

641
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:11,390
I'm approaching the
artery of Percheron.

642
00:33:12,190 --> 00:33:14,386
I'm one millimeter
from the clot.

643
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:15,459
Stop right there.

644
00:33:20,765 --> 00:33:24,429
If we disrupt this clot, we could
cause a shower of emboli into her brain.

645
00:33:47,659 --> 00:33:49,218
Deploying the retriever.

646
00:33:52,898 --> 00:33:55,561
- EEG just went flatline.
- Calm down. I'm almost...

647
00:33:58,470 --> 00:33:59,470
Got it.

648
00:34:05,844 --> 00:34:07,904
Blood's flowing
through the artery.

649
00:34:07,979 --> 00:34:09,504
Her brain tracing's
looking better.

650
00:34:16,354 --> 00:34:20,348
This should fill the gap between
the inferior and superior vena cava

651
00:34:20,425 --> 00:34:22,417
when the new
chambers get sewn in.

652
00:34:22,494 --> 00:34:23,792
Where's that graft?

653
00:34:24,596 --> 00:34:26,596
I need more sponges. The
bleeding is getting worse.

654
00:34:26,631 --> 00:34:28,376
Ah, he's tanking.

655
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,400
Can you push epi?

656
00:34:29,467 --> 00:34:30,730
I already did. He's maxing out.

657
00:34:30,802 --> 00:34:32,998
I'm running out of ways
to keep his pressure up.

658
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:35,802
I got it. They had
205 centimeters of it.

659
00:34:36,575 --> 00:34:37,599
Thank you.

660
00:34:38,443 --> 00:34:40,571
If you want to gown up, you
can watch from down here.

661
00:34:40,645 --> 00:34:42,307
Definitely. Thanks.

662
00:34:44,849 --> 00:34:47,614
I thought telling her how much I
love her in front of other people

663
00:34:47,686 --> 00:34:48,984
would make her feel good.

664
00:34:49,054 --> 00:34:52,752
But Dr. Guerin said I made
her feel insecure and scared.

665
00:34:53,491 --> 00:34:54,789
Women are sensitive.

666
00:34:55,527 --> 00:34:57,553
When commenting on their flaws,

667
00:34:57,629 --> 00:35:00,121
total honesty is a
high-risk procedure.

668
00:35:00,198 --> 00:35:01,598
That sounds sexist.

669
00:35:01,666 --> 00:35:04,261
Aren't men also
insecure about their flaws?

670
00:35:04,336 --> 00:35:07,602
Men are much, much worse.
And also, we're really stupid.

671
00:35:07,672 --> 00:35:11,234
Okay, what can I do now?

672
00:35:11,309 --> 00:35:13,869
I've already said
my stupid stuff.

673
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:15,971
I don't want her to
be upset with me.

674
00:35:18,283 --> 00:35:19,307
I have a thought.

675
00:35:21,753 --> 00:35:24,086
I think this run of sutures
will hold it to the annulus,

676
00:35:24,155 --> 00:35:25,316
but I'm worried about leaks.

677
00:35:25,390 --> 00:35:28,918
We can put a second row of pledgeted
sutures to make sure it's hemostatic.

678
00:35:28,994 --> 00:35:30,758
That is unreal.

679
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:33,595
It's a work of art.

680
00:35:35,667 --> 00:35:36,896
Now let's get it back in

681
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:39,164
while we can still get
him off bypass alive.

682
00:35:43,708 --> 00:35:45,301
Reperfusing the heart.

683
00:35:47,178 --> 00:35:51,172
We've got a rhythm.

684
00:36:19,878 --> 00:36:20,902
Hey.

685
00:36:22,714 --> 00:36:25,878
There was a complication
during the reconstruction surgery.

686
00:36:26,951 --> 00:36:29,819
A clot, which caused
you to lapse into a coma.

687
00:36:31,322 --> 00:36:34,952
We performed a second surgery
on your brain, which was successful.

688
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:36,085
Um...

689
00:36:36,161 --> 00:36:37,424
You're gonna be fine.

690
00:36:37,829 --> 00:36:38,888
But my breasts?

691
00:36:39,497 --> 00:36:43,696
The clot occurred after we
finished inserting the implants.

692
00:36:46,538 --> 00:36:48,905
I think you're gonna be
very pleased with the results.

693
00:36:50,608 --> 00:36:51,769
Thank you.

694
00:36:52,243 --> 00:36:53,243
Yeah.

695
00:36:59,617 --> 00:37:02,883
I think I'm sorry.

696
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:10,187
Dr. Guerin said I should
never say anything

697
00:37:10,261 --> 00:37:12,924
that might sound
negative to a girlfriend.

698
00:37:12,997 --> 00:37:17,196
And Dr. Glassman said total
honesty is a high-risk procedure

699
00:37:18,002 --> 00:37:19,002
with a girlfriend.

700
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:22,234
It's better to show my
love than try to explain it.

701
00:37:25,210 --> 00:37:30,774
But I want to be
totally honest with you.

702
00:37:37,122 --> 00:37:38,818
I don't like your body...

703
00:37:39,591 --> 00:37:41,719
because it's excellent.

704
00:37:41,793 --> 00:37:43,728
I like it because it's yours.

705
00:37:46,564 --> 00:37:50,467
And I love hearing you talk.

706
00:37:50,535 --> 00:37:52,128
When I hear your voice,

707
00:37:52,804 --> 00:37:55,865
especially when I've
had a difficult day,

708
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:57,738
I find it comforting.

709
00:38:02,981 --> 00:38:05,143
Now I want to hug you. Can I?

710
00:38:06,151 --> 00:38:07,449
I'd like that.

711
00:38:18,363 --> 00:38:19,456
I love you.

712
00:38:21,166 --> 00:38:22,225
Thank you...

713
00:38:23,601 --> 00:38:25,570
for your total honesty.

714
00:38:32,877 --> 00:38:34,277
Your surgery went well.

715
00:38:34,345 --> 00:38:37,144
With some time and rehab, you
should be back to work in a month.

716
00:38:37,682 --> 00:38:38,682
Thank you.

717
00:38:39,017 --> 00:38:41,213
Don't thank me.
Thank your surgeon.

718
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:43,614
She did all the important stuff.

719
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:50,690
Lim's golden boy is in.
Nothing we can do about that.

720
00:38:50,762 --> 00:38:52,663
So that leaves three openings.

721
00:38:52,730 --> 00:38:55,962
The thought of working with Will
Hooper for the next two years...

722
00:38:56,034 --> 00:38:58,128
If Dr. Lim thinks he'll
be a good resident,

723
00:38:58,203 --> 00:38:59,967
I'm sure she has good reasons.

724
00:39:00,038 --> 00:39:03,805
She probably thinks arrogance
is helpful to a surgeon.

725
00:39:03,875 --> 00:39:05,810
Well, we could try
to change her mind.

726
00:39:05,877 --> 00:39:08,142
Nah, she asked us to
evaluate the applicants, not her.

727
00:39:08,213 --> 00:39:11,047
She asked us to
be totally honest.

728
00:39:11,115 --> 00:39:13,175
Yeah, "totally honest"
is a relative term

729
00:39:13,251 --> 00:39:15,652
when you're telling your
boss she's totally wrong.

730
00:39:19,457 --> 00:39:21,358
So Hooper's in. Who else?

731
00:39:21,426 --> 00:39:24,487
Dr. Andrews likes
Dr. Jordan Allen.

732
00:39:24,562 --> 00:39:26,087
I do too.

733
00:39:26,164 --> 00:39:27,723
She's confident, driven.

734
00:39:27,799 --> 00:39:29,279
She won't take a
lot of hand-holding,

735
00:39:29,334 --> 00:39:31,428
and keeping Andrews
happy keeps us happy.

736
00:39:31,502 --> 00:39:34,336
- Mm.
- That leaves two more. Who's next?

737
00:39:35,173 --> 00:39:39,338
Asher Wolke is very
up-front about who he is.

738
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:40,275
I like that.

739
00:39:40,345 --> 00:39:41,870
He's definitely eager.

740
00:39:41,946 --> 00:39:43,608
And he couldn't be
more open to learning.

741
00:39:43,681 --> 00:39:46,207
Ah, agree. That leaves one more.

742
00:39:47,652 --> 00:39:49,052
John Lundberg.

743
00:39:50,255 --> 00:39:53,248
Smart, professional,
mature. He's a no-brainer.

744
00:39:54,192 --> 00:39:55,192
Lundberg's in.

745
00:39:55,693 --> 00:39:56,717
Lundberg's out.

746
00:39:57,262 --> 00:39:59,231
He stopped by my
office before he left,

747
00:39:59,297 --> 00:40:01,266
said he's no longer interested.

748
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:05,461
He said you all
were unprofessional.

749
00:40:06,304 --> 00:40:07,863
Drinking at work.

750
00:40:08,606 --> 00:40:11,974
Asking inappropriate
questions. Dating drama.

751
00:40:13,912 --> 00:40:16,438
Mm-hm. So who's your alt?

752
00:40:16,514 --> 00:40:18,779
Olivia Jackson or Board Shorts?

753
00:40:20,251 --> 00:40:23,119
Olivia knows her stuff,
but she's a bit insecure.

754
00:40:23,922 --> 00:40:26,414
Her answers
sound like questions.

755
00:40:26,491 --> 00:40:29,154
I like Board Shorts.
He's sensitive.

756
00:40:29,227 --> 00:40:30,320
Like a woman.

757
00:40:35,833 --> 00:40:37,961
I vote for both of them.

758
00:40:38,703 --> 00:40:41,104
That's not an option.
We don't have the budget.

759
00:40:43,408 --> 00:40:44,432
Hooper is the worst.

760
00:40:45,910 --> 00:40:47,242
The person I said was the best?

761
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:50,908
He is arrogant and obnoxious.

762
00:40:50,982 --> 00:40:54,282
If he works here, we'll
hate him, the work will suffer,

763
00:40:54,352 --> 00:40:57,789
and we'll either kill
patients or we'll kill him.

764
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,093
And there is no way
that you don't see that,

765
00:41:06,164 --> 00:41:07,462
which makes me think...

766
00:41:10,635 --> 00:41:11,635
you do.

767
00:41:13,037 --> 00:41:14,037
This was a test.

768
00:41:15,340 --> 00:41:19,004
You just wanted to see
if we'd be totally honest.

769
00:41:21,045 --> 00:41:22,274
Well done.

770
00:41:23,348 --> 00:41:25,817
Hooper is definitely the worst.

771
00:41:25,883 --> 00:41:28,409
I only let him shadow as
a favor to a board member.

772
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:31,547
I figured I'd give him a second
chance after his obnoxious interview.

773
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:34,318
And also do a little experiment.

774
00:41:37,295 --> 00:41:38,295
So...

775
00:41:39,297 --> 00:41:41,198
it's Jordan,

776
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:46,169
Asher, Olivia and Enrique.

777
00:41:48,906 --> 00:41:51,341
To the next phase of
your surgical training.

778
00:41:51,409 --> 00:41:52,843
You helped pick them.

779
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:55,505
As senior residents, it's now
your job to help train them.

780
00:41:56,214 --> 00:41:58,308
And don't take this
responsibility lightly,

781
00:41:58,383 --> 00:42:01,512
because if you don't train
them well, people will die.
